## 2023/12/20 Updates 1.0.2 (bug fixes) 🚨 

We have detected some miners that are spoofing their performances.

Issues Addressed:
- Ensure validators are now able to blacklist hotkeys of malicious miners.
- Provide a list of suspected malicious hotkeys (this list can evolve very fast and we are constantly checking and benchmarking results / signatures)

To take advantage of the blacklist hotkeys feature, include the `--blacklisted.hotkeys` and add a list of the hotkeys that is suspected to be malicious when running your processes. 

Example:
```sh
cd neurons
python -m validator.py
  ...  # your args
  --blacklisted.hotkeys "['hotkey_x', 'hotkey_y', '...']"
```
By default the blacklisted.hotkeys is an empty list.

To take advantage of our internal suspected list of hotkeys, simply include the `--blacklist.suspected.hotkeys` when running your processes. 

Example:
```sh
cd neurons
python -m validator.py
  ...  # your args
  --blacklist.suspected.hotkeys
```
By default the blacklist.suspected.hotkeys is an set to False and when flagged sets it to True.

**Validators** This argument is highly recommended asap. 🚨 

GitHub PRs

https://github.com/neuralinternet/compute-subnet/pull/81

### Actions required

**Validators mandatory** 🚨  And please stay aware about the potential next spoofers while we fix totally this issue.

**Miners** if you want to skip to missmatch version

Please pull the latest code and restart the already-running process using pm2 restart all command.

For example:
```sh
cd compute-subnet
git pull
pm2 restart all 
```

Happy mining / validating

Neural Internet
